contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox protected area of Australia | name = Wallingat National Park | iucn_category = II | map = | map_caption = | locator_x = | locator_y = | location = | nearest_town_or_city= |coordinates = {{Coord|32|18|04|S|152|26|07|E|type:landmark_region:AU-NSW|display=inline,title}} | area = {{Convert|65.57|km2|sqmi|2|abbr=on}} | established = 1999 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | managing_authorities = [[National Parks and Wildlife Service (New South Wales)|NSW National Parks and Wildlife Service]] | official_site = http://www.nationalparks.nsw.gov.au }} '''Wallingat''' is a national park in [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]], 211 km northeast of [[Sydney, Australia|Sydney]]. The park has forest walks, a campsite on the banks of the [[Wallingat River]] and a viewpoint, the Whoota Whoota Lookout, with views of [[Wallis Lake]] and the coast.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/news/travel/from-booti-booti-to-boomerang/2007/11/29/1196530525221.html|title=From Booti Booti to Boomerang|last=Scott|first=Daniel|date=3 December 2007|work=Brisbane Times|accessdate=15 August 2010}}</ref> The roads are unsealed and narrow, but suitable for two wheel drive vehicles in dry weather.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greatlakes.org.au/accom_result1/wallingat-national-park-camping/|title=Wallingat National Park Camping|work=Great Lakes Tourism|accessdate=15 August 2010}}</ref> ==See also== * [[Protected areas of New South Wales]] ==References== <references/> ==External links== {{commons category}} *[http://www.environment.nsw.gov.au/NationalParks/parkHome.aspx?id=N0132 Wallingat National Park], NSW Government *[http://www.environment.nsw.gov.au/parkmanagement/WallingatDraftMgmtplan.htm Wallingat National Park - draft plan of management].
